#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is DVB?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:39
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<e>DVB</e> stands for <e>Digital Video Broadcasting</e>. DVB describes methods\n"
"to transfer digital data of TV, radio, interactive services like MHP, EPG and\n"
"teletext. Through data compression with MPEG-2, or H.264 for HDTV, it's\n"
"possible to transfer several channels on the same frequency. The more data\n"
"compression, the more channels can be transferred, but you pay it with quality\n"
"loss.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:48
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"DVB can be transferred in several ways. The trailing letter identifies the\n"
"method of transfer, e.g. DVB-<e>T</e> for terrestrial transmission. There are\n"
"several more types:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "DVB-S for transmission over satellites"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "DVB-C for transmission over cable"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "DVB-H for transmission to mobile devices (terrestrial)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "DVB-IPI for transmission over IP based networks, e.g. internet"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:59
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    DVB-RC(S/C/T) return channel for the transmission of data services, e.g.\n"
"    broadband internet\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "Types and requirement of DVB cards"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Besides the different methods available to receive a DVB stream, the cards are\n"
"classified by their type of produced output. There are cards with a decoder\n"
"implemented which offer direct access to the stream by the device\n"
"<path>/dev/video</path>. These cards are <e>full featured cards</e>.  Other\n"
"cards have no own decoder implemented and require a software decoder on the\n"
"computer and are <e>budget cards</e>. This implies higher system requirements.\n"
"Your computer's CPU should run at at least 600 MHz, and have at least 256MB of\n"
"RAM. <uri link=\"http://linuxtv.org/wiki/index.php/DVB_Card_Vendors\">This\n"
"list</uri> is useful for identifying your card.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preparing the system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:90
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring the kernel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:94
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, we must ensure that your kernel supports DVB and your DVB device. Since\n"
"kernel version 2.6 the necessary drivers are included. Check your kernel\n"
"configuration and make sure the following options are selected as a static\n"
"driver or as modules.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:100
#, no-wrap
msgid "Required kernel options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:101
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Input Device Support ---&gt;\n"
"* Event Interface\n"
"Device Drivers ---&gt;\n"
"Multimedia Devices ---&gt;\n"
"Digital Video Broadcasting Devices ---&gt;\n"
"    [*] DVB For Linux\n"
"     *  DVB Core Support\n"
"   M  [Your driver]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:112
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Additionally we have to select the proper driver for your hardware. To find out\n"
"the right module for your card, we mark every driver as module. If you have a\n"
"PCI card, install <c>pciutils</c> if you haven't already. If you want built-in\n"
"drivers or you don't own a PCI card, skip this step and continue with <uri\n"
"link=\"#kernel_output\">Checking the kernel output</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing pciutils"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:120
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge pciutils</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After booting the new kernel, we run <c>pcimodules</c> to list the required\n"
"modules.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:128
#, no-wrap
msgid "Listing the required modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>pcimodules</i>\n"
"ohci-hcd\n"
"ehci-hcd\n"
"sis900\n"
"snd-emu10k1\n"
"b2c2-flexcop-pci\n"
"nvidia\n"
"nvidiafb\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In this case we have to load the module <c>b2c2-flexcop-pci</c>. We add the\n"
"name to <path>/etc/conf.d/modules</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:144
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding the module name"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:145
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano -w /etc/conf.d/modules</i>\n"
"\n"
"modules=\"<i>b2c2-flexcop-pci</i>\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:154
#, no-wrap
msgid "Checking the kernel output"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:158
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It's recommended to mark every driver as module, so that you can add the\n"
"required module dynamically, especially if you don't know the module name. If\n"
"you already know the module name, select the driver as a built-in driver.\n"
"Compile the kernel, install the modules and boot it. You can check if your\n"
"kernel has successfully detected your card by using <c>dmesg</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "Checking kernel output"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:166
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>dmesg | grep DVB</i>\n"
"<comment>(If you own a TerraTec Cinergy T2, your output might look like this:)</comment>\n"
"DVB: registering new adaptor (TerraTec/qanu USB2.0 Highspeed DVB-T Receiver).\n"
"input: TerraTec/qanu USB2.0 Highspeed DVB-T Receiver remote control as /class/input/input2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:177 en/vdr-guide.xml:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing VDR"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:182
#, no-wrap
msgid "To install VDR, we just emerge it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:186
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge vdr</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:190
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now continue with <uri link=\"#inst_ir_remote\">Installing the Remote Control</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:198
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing the Remote Control"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:203
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There are at least two ways to control VDR via an infrared remote control. If\n"
"your TV card has an onboard IR receiver you can use <c>vdr-remote</c>.\n"
"Otherwise, you most likely need to use LIRC.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:211 en/vdr-guide.xml:218
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing vdr-remote"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "We first install the plugin via emerge:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:219
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge vdr-remote</i>\n"
"# <i>eselect vdr-plugin enable remote</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:224
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When using the remote plugin for the IR port on your DVB card everything should\n"
"be fine with the default config. It automatically uses the input device which\n"
"has \"dvb\" in its name. For more advanced uses take a look at\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/vdr.remote</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:231
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now, continue with <uri link=\"#video-out\">Video Output Methods</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:237
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternative: installing LIRC"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:241
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your card can be remotely controlled (but you cannot or do not want to use\n"
"<c>vdr-remote</c>), you may wish to configure LIRC. LIRC interprets the pressed\n"
"keys and returns a name for each one. A program that supports LIRC waits for key\n"
"events and runs the action configured in the config file, mostly stored in the\n"
"config directory of the executing program (e.g.  <c>mplayer</c> loads the file\n"
"<path>~/.mplayer/lircrc</path>). Before we install LIRC, you have to add\n"
"<c>lirc</c> to your USE flags and add an additional entry to\n"
"<path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path>: <c>LIRC_DEVICES</c>. Use <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.lirc.org/html/table.html\">this list</uri> to find the proper\n"
"arguments for the option.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:253
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing LIRC"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:254
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano -w /etc/portage/make.conf</i>\n"
"<comment>(Replace \"devinput\" with the proper driver)</comment>\n"
"LIRC_DEVICES=\"devinput\"\n"
"USE=\"lirc\"\n"
"# <i>emerge lirc</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:262
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"At first we have to define each key code with a name. Most supported remote\n"
"controls are configured already, take a look at the <uri\n"
"link=\"http://lirc.sourceforge.net/remotes/\">remote list</uri>. Download the\n"
"required file and save it as <path>/etc/lircd.conf</path>. Now we have to find\n"
"out where to access your remote control. Run the following command to get a\n"
"list of the current input devices (make sure your device is running).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:270
#, no-wrap
msgid "List of current input devices"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:271
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>cat /proc/bus/input/devices</i>\n"
"I: Bus=0000 Vendor=0000 Product=0000 Version=0000\n"
"N: Name=\"TerraTec/qanu USB2.0 Highspeed DVB-T Receiver remote control\"\n"
"P: Phys=usb-0000:00:1d.7-1/input0\n"
"S: Sysfs=/class/input/input2\n"
"H: Handlers=kbd event1\n"
"B: EV=100003\n"
"B: KEY=108fc210 2043 0 0 0 0 8000 2080 1 9e1680 0 0 ffc\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:282
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In this case we have the Terratec Cinergy T2 device plugged in, so we can\n"
"access the device over <path>/dev/input/event1</path>. Replace <c>event1</c>\n"
"with the matching device in your output.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:288
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>lircd</c> needs to know the device to use. Add the following line to\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/lircd</path>. Remember to replace <c>devinput</c> with\n"
"the name of your driver and <c>event1</c> with the actual device.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:293
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding options to lircd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:294
#, no-wrap
msgid "LIRCD_OPTS=\"-H devinput -d /dev/input/event1\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:298
#, no-wrap
msgid "It's time to start <c>lircd</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:301
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting lircd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:302
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>/etc/init.d/lircd start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:306
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now it should be possible to watch <c>lircd</c> capturing and decoding key\n"
"presses. Just run the command <c>irw</c>. Stop it by pressing Ctrl+C when you\n"
"have enough.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:311
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing LIRC"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:312
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>irw</i>\n"
"0000000000001aa2 00 Exit Technisat_TTS35AI.conf\n"
"0000000000001a8d 00 Mute Technisat_TTS35AI.conf\n"
"0000000000000a97 00 OK Technisat_TTS35AI.conf\n"
"0000000000000a97 01 OK Technisat_TTS35AI.conf\n"
"0000000000000a92 00 Menu Technisat_TTS35AI.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:321
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next, add it to the default runlevel so that it starts automatically at boot.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:324
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding lircd to the default runlevel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:325
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>rc-update add lircd default</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:329
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To be able to use your remote control, you must enable LIRC support in VDR. Add\n"
"the following line to <path>/etc/conf.d/vdr</path>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:333
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling support for LIRC"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:334
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano -w /etc/conf.d/vdr</i>\n"
"IR_CTRL=\"lirc\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:343
#, no-wrap
msgid "Video Output Methods"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:348
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You now need to decide on one (and only one!) of the following video output\n"
"devices which show the picture and the overlayed On Screen Display (OSD).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:355
#, no-wrap
msgid "Hardware decoding: full-featured DVB cards"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:359
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Users of these expensive cards need not install anything else, so you may\n"
"continue with <uri link=\"#channel_list\">configuring your channel list</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:366
#, no-wrap
msgid "Hardware decoding: DXR3/Hollywood+ cards"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:370
#, no-wrap
msgid "To use a DXR3 card for VDR output we need the <c>vdr-dxr3</c> plugin.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:373
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing the plugin"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:374
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge vdr-dxr3</i>\n"
"# <i>nano -w /etc/conf.d/modules</i>\n"
"\n"
"modules=\"<i>em8300</i>\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:381
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The em8300 module need some configuration that depends on the exact revision of\n"
"that card.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:393 en/vdr-guide.xml:418 en/vdr-guide.xml:458
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:522
#, no-wrap
msgid "Continue with <uri link=\"#channel_list\">configuring your channel list</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:399
#, no-wrap
msgid "Hardware decoding: PVR350 cards"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:403
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As PVR350 cards have an onboard MPEG-Decoder chip we want to make use of that.\n"
"We need to install the <c>vdr-pvr350</c> plugin.  If <c>ivtv-driver</c> is not\n"
"yet installed emerge will automatically install it for you. To have the ivtv\n"
"module loaded at boot we add it to\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/modules</path>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:410
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing PVR350-Plugin"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:411
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge vdr-pvr350</i>\n"
"# <i>nano -w /etc/conf.d/modules</i>\n"
"\n"
"modules=\"<i>ivtv</i>\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:424
#, no-wrap
msgid "Software decoding: vdr-softdevice"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:428
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To install it, we have to emerge <c>vdr-softdevice</c>. Don't forget\n"
"to enable the plugin.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:432
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing the softdevice plugin"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:433
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge vdr-softdevice</i>\n"
"# <i>eselect vdr-plugin enable softdevice</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:438
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To select the proper video and audio output, edit\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/vdr.softdevice</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:443
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For now, we will only describe the shm (\"shared memory\") method. This is already\n"
"enabled in the installed config file (Setting SOFTDEVICE_VIDEO_OUT). Later you\n"
"need to start <c>ShmClient</c> to get a window showing the picture.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:449
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you do not want to think about a separate keyboard layout for controlling\n"
"VDR, there are remote configuration files available at Matthias Schwarzott's\n"
"<uri link=\"http://dev.gentoo.org/~zzam/vdr_remote_conf/\">devspace</uri>. There\n"
"are files for softdevice/shm and xineliboutput (more coming). You will need the\n"
"relevant file to <path>/etc/vdr/remote.conf</path> and run <c>chown vdr:vdr</c>\n"
"on the file to get it working.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:464
#, no-wrap
msgid "Software decoding: vdr-xineliboutput"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:468
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Some people prefer to use <c>vdr-xineliboutput</c>, because it can also work\n"
"remotely. We'll now teach you how to configure <c>vdr-xineliboutput</c> on your\n"
"host and client. First, the host setup:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:473
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing vdr-xineliboutput"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:474
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge vdr-xineliboutput</i>\n"
"# <i>eselect vdr-plugin enable xineliboutput</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:479
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Adding command line options at this point is crucial for xineliboutput to work.\n"
"For more options, see <c>vdr --help</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:483
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding command line options to /etc/conf.d/vdr.xineliboutput"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:484
#, no-wrap
msgid "_EXTRAOPTS=\"--local=none --remote=37890\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:488
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The next step is to edit <path>/etc/vdr/svdrphosts.conf</path>. This file\n"
"describes a number of host addresses that are allowed to connect to the SVDRP\n"
"port of the video disk recorder running on the host system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:493
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing /etc/vdr/svdrphosts.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:494
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(The proper syntax is: IP-Address[/Netmask])</comment>\n"
"127.0.0.1             <comment>(always accept localhost)</comment>\n"
"192.168.1.0/24        <comment>(any host on the local net)</comment>\n"
"#204.152.189.113      <comment>(a specific host)</comment>\n"
"#0.0.0.0/0            <comment>(any host on any net - USE THIS WITH CARE!)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:502
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you only want to use <c>vdr-xineliboutput</c> to view the picture on the same\n"
"computer as the one running VDR you can continue with <uri\n"
"link=\"#channel_list\">configuring your channel list</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:508
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Otherwise, you now simply <c>emerge media-plugins/vdr-xineliboutput</c> on your\n"
"client:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:512
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:513
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge vdr-xineliboutput</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:517
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Later (after having started VDR) you will use the command <c>vdr-sxfe\n"
"xvdr://hostname</c> to connect to VDR and view its picture and OSD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:526
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There is also a plugin which just simulates the existance of a real\n"
"output device (<c>vdr-dummydevice</c>) for some fancy uses like record-only\n"
"servers, but that is more advanced than a normal VDR setup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:536
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a Channel List"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:541
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To make VDR really useful you need to create an appropriate channel list. There\n"
"is more than one way to get a working list of channels (besides downloading\n"
"one). The channel list installed by default is for DVB-S reception on Astra on\n"
"19.2°E.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:550
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using dvbscan from linuxtv-dvb-apps"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:553
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing linuxtv-dvb-apps"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:554
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge linuxtv-dvb-apps</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:558
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Find the correct frequency list for your region and type of reception.  These\n"
"files are stored under <path>/usr/share/dvb/scan</path>.  For reception with\n"
"DVB-T in Germany, Region Nuernberg you need to use\n"
"<path>/usr/share/dvb/scan/dvb-t/de-Nuernberg</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:564
#, no-wrap
msgid "Scanning with dvbscan"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:565
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>dvbscan -o vdr /usr/share/dvb/scan/dvb-t/de-Nuernberg &gt; /etc/vdr/channels.conf</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:571
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using vdr-reelchannelscan"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:575
#, no-wrap
msgid "First, delete the contents of the existing channel list.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:578
#, no-wrap
msgid "Cleaning old channel-list"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:579
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>rm /etc/vdr/channels.conf</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:582
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing and activating vdr-reelchannelscan"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:583
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge vdr-reelchannelscan</i>\n"
"# <i>eselect vdr-plugin enable reelchannelscan</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:590
#, no-wrap
msgid "Channels for systems using vdr-analogtv"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:594
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You'll probably want to configure your channels at this point. The VDR project\n"
"provides you with some examples which can be found at\n"
"<path>/usr/share/doc/vdr-analogtv-$version/examples/</path>, as long as you've\n"
"installed &gt;=<c>media-plugins/vdr-analogtv-1.0.00-r1</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:605 en/vdr-guide.xml:635
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting VDR"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:610
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After having all basic software parts ready on the system you need to\n"
"configure VDR with its OSD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:615
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you use a hardware decoder for picture output you should switch on the\n"
"connected TV now. If you use software output the client for this must be started\n"
"after VDR.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:621
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, you should learn your key definitions; that is, connecting keys on your\n"
"remote control to VDR's internal commands.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:626
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Just in case you need to edit the keyboard configuration, or (more likely) want\n"
"to delete it to go back to learning the keys: VDR stores its key-definitions in\n"
"<path>/etc/vdr/remote.conf</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:632
#, no-wrap
msgid "We begin with starting VDR:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:636
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>/etc/init.d/vdr start</i>\n"
"* Preparing start of vdr:\n"
"*   config files ...                                        [ ok ]\n"
"*   Waiting for prerequisites (devices nodes etc.) ...      [ ok ]\n"
"* Starting vdr ...                                          [ ok ]\n"
"* First start of vdr: No check for running vdr possible\n"
"* until control device (remote/keyboard) keys are learnt!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:646
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Users of software decoders should now start the client program that opens the\n"
"window to show the TV picture and the OSD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:650
#, no-wrap
msgid "Activating the software decoder for the client"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:651
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(For users of vdr-softdevice)</comment>\n"
"# <i>ShmClient</i>\n"
"<comment>(For users of vdr-xineliboutput)</comment>\n"
"# <i>vdr-sxfe xvdr://hostname</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:658
#, no-wrap
msgid "The most useful keys for VDR are:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:661
#, no-wrap
msgid "Cursor keys (Left/Right/Up/Down)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:662
#, no-wrap
msgid "Menu/Exit/Ok"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:663
#, no-wrap
msgid "Colors (Red/Green/Yellow/Blue)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:664
#, no-wrap
msgid "Number keys (0-9)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:668
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you don't have many keys, make sure to assign these. (Some remotes have\n"
"Play/Pause/etc. on the same keys as the colors, so use them for the colors).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:673
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that the basic installation is over, you need to configure VDR. Switch to\n"
"your output screen and follow the on-screen instructions. VDR asks you to press\n"
"various keys on your remote control to learn the correct key codes. If you don't\n"
"own a remote control, you can use your keyboard.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:684
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now you can add the VDR initscript to the default runlevel to get it started\n"
"every time your computer boots up.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:688
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding vdr to the default runlevel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:689
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>rc-update add vdr default</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:697
#, no-wrap
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/vdr-guide.xml:702
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you need any help, you can always ask someone in <uri\n"
"link=\"irc://irc.gentoo.org/gentoo-vdr\">#gentoo-vdr</uri>, or look around on our\n"
"<uri link=\"http://forums.gentoo.org/\">forums</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""
